1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:09,427
Everybody needs a second room

2
00:00:09,577 --> 00:00:14,003
A place to hide, a place to bloom

3
00:00:14,153 --> 00:00:18,580
Mom has one, but don’t say where

4
00:00:18,730 --> 00:00:23,157
It’s secret like next week’s dinner fare

5
00:00:23,307 --> 00:00:27,733
My sister has a second too

6
00:00:27,883 --> 00:00:32,310
A style quite different, it’s red, not
blue

7
00:00:32,460 --> 00:00:36,887
She calls it home, the Rat Palace lives

8
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:41,463
With hammocks, tubes, and snacks she gives

9
00:00:41,613 --> 00:00:46,040
One year we made the space for mine

10
00:00:46,190 --> 00:00:50,617
Cleared out Dad’s old Zoom call shrine

11
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:55,193
He’s got a second house, it’s fair

12
00:00:55,343 --> 00:00:59,770
So now I’ve got four walls and air

13
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:04,347
My second room has no light switch

14
00:01:04,497 --> 00:01:08,923
Just a glow I didn’t pick

15
00:01:09,073 --> 00:01:13,500
Overhead, it hums too bright

16
00:01:13,650 --> 00:01:18,077
It stays on day and night

17
00:01:18,227 --> 00:01:22,653
It must mean something — I can’t say which

18
00:01:22,803 --> 00:01:27,230
But my second room has no light switch

19
00:01:27,380 --> 00:01:31,807
I placed some screens from old Japan

20
00:01:31,957 --> 00:01:36,383
They fold like waves, they stand, not hang

21
00:01:36,533 --> 00:01:40,960
A mountain scene, a paper crane

22
00:01:41,110 --> 00:01:45,537
A wall that doesn’t quite explain

23
00:01:45,687 --> 00:01:50,113
There’s no bed, just a desk and chair

24
00:01:50,263 --> 00:01:54,690
A chalkboard waits with chalk to spare

25
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:59,267
No clicks, no off, just quiet beams

26
00:01:59,417 --> 00:02:03,843
And maybe that’s what silence means

27
00:02:03,993 --> 00:02:08,420
My second room has no light switch

28
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:12,997
Just a truth you learn but can’t quite fix

29
00:02:13,147 --> 00:02:17,573
Overhead, the quiet burn

30
00:02:17,723 --> 00:02:22,150
Like someone left it on, forgot to return

31
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:26,727
It feels like something soft and stitched

32
00:02:26,877 --> 00:02:31,303
In my second room with no light switch

33
00:02:31,453 --> 00:02:35,880
One day I might ask why that is

34
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:40,457
Or maybe I won’t — it just exists

35
00:02:40,607 --> 00:02:45,033
Some things you live with, some you ditch

36
00:02:45,183 --> 00:02:49,610
Like my second room with no light switch
